add_hide_invis

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
add_hide_invis -  This method adds a hide/invis state to the object.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int add_hide_invis(string type,
object who,
mixed see,
string * gone)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^type%^RESET%^ - the name of the type of hiding
%^BOLD%^who%^RESET%^ - no idea
%^BOLD%^see%^RESET%^ - no idea
%^BOLD%^gone%^RESET%^ - the method and object to call when the hiding is removed
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
1 on success, 0 on failure

.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/basic/hide_invis.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method adds a hide/invis state to the object.
